  "original_title": "\u0d95\u0dc3\u0dca\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dda\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dba 46\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "46 deported to Australia",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Australian Coast Guard arrested 46 Sri Lankans who were attempting to enter Australia illegally and deported them to the Katunayake International Airport on a special Australian flight this morning (30).",
        "They are residents of Chilaw and include two children under the age of five.",
        "This group had arrived at Katunayake Airport at 08.40 this morning (30th) from Cocos Island by special flight ASY-978 belonging to Australia.",
        "More than 100 Sri Lankan security personnel were on board the plane, along with Sri Lankans.",
        "A team of officials from the Australian High Commission in Sri Lanka arrived at the Katunayake Airport and took steps to receive the Sri Lankans on board and hand over the Katunayake Airport to the Immigration and Emigration Department.",
        "The group of Sri Lankans were later transferred to the National Intelligence Service at the airport and later to the CID at the Katunayake Airport.",
        "After taking statements from them, they are to be produced before the Negombo Magistrate's Court."
      ],
